Defendant in custody on WRIT.
Count 2, PTC theft-movable property - No contest plea.  Convicted.  

Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for forty-two (42) months.  Eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by two (2) years extended supervision, concurrent with all sentences defendant is presently serving.
The defendant is found eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)   Pay restitution of $1,000.00 joint and several with Brett Holtz paid to Capitol Insurance for the Lewis Claim and $663.49 paid to Brett Holtz (co-defendant Holtz paid all out of pocket expenses to Chris Lewis);
2)   COMPAS assessment;
3)   Maintain full-time employment or work search;
4)   AODA treatment as directed;
5)   No contact with Brandon Rabe, Karen Kratz, Brett Holtz, Chris Lewis and his place of business, Stacy Schweitzer and her residence, Kenneth Alfson and his residence, Jay Goldman and John Kunesh;
6)   Random drug screens and pays for same;
7)   Maintain absolute sobriety;
8)   Submit a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
9)   Pay costs of the action ($500.00 cash bail to be applied); and 
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.

Court dismisses and reads in count 1, felony bail jumping, as well as the uncharged misdemeanor theft offenses from the following Manitowoc County Sheriffs Department referrals:  14-2676, 14-1428, 14-1483, 14-1970, 14-2589, 14-2660, 14-2662, 14-2663, 14-2665 and 14-1999.

Court orders the defendant to make restitution payments from any earnings made while in prison and that restitution be paid first to citizen victims, then to co-defendant Brett Holtz and then to Capitol Insurance.
Defendant is to be given 60 days jail credit.  If Attorney Pangburn can prove the defendant has the 3 extra days of jail credit, the Court wil consider it.
